race.comment: BRULLEN (1) is racing well and looks a key chance here. He rode the speed at Mornington last time over 1500m and stuck on gamely for second in a 0-62, beaten under a length. Drops back in class for this and should take plenty of running down. BONNAROO (3) is back sharply in trip from 2000m last time at Ballarat but had been going well over the shorter trips prior. Second at Warrnambool over this trip three back in a BM64 is good form although she likely gives them a decent start. SAKASU (8) has just found one better at his past couple and rates an each way chance again. JAZ TYCOON (4) is going okay, just finding one better last time out. Can sneak another placing.
